# Token savings (mandatory)

Global hooks at `~/.cursor/hooks.json` also apply. This project has `.codegraph/` indexed.

## CodeGraph — use MCP first

Before Read/Grep/SemanticSearch exploration loops:

1. Call `codegraph_explore` (user-codegraph MCP) for architecture, flows, "how does X work", pre-edit surveys.
2. Use `codegraph_node` for one symbol/file with callers/callees.
3. Use `codegraph_callers` before refactors.
4. Use `codegraph_search` to locate symbols by name.

Trust CodeGraph output — do not re-verify with grep unless staleness banner says file pending re-index.

Skip CodeGraph only for configs, docs, or non-indexed paths.

## RTK — compact shell output

For git, tests, builds, npm, pip, and other noisy CLI commands, prefix with `rtk`:

```powershell
rtk git status
rtk npm test
rtk python -m pytest
```

Do not wrap: interactive commands, `rtk` itself, `codegraph`, or one-liners that must stay raw.

Prefer RTK output over piping huge logs into context.

## Caveman

Keep responses terse when user invokes caveman mode. Technical accuracy unchanged.
